# .dockerignore for the GRACE-2 agent image (services/agent/Dockerfile).
#
# The build context is the repo ROOT (the CodeBuild buildspec sets it so the
# COPY paths are repo-root-relative, matching the worker images). This file is
# read when the build context root is services/agent/ -- it keeps the agent
# subtree lean. The codebuild buildspec also tars only services/agent into the
# context, so most of these are belt-and-suspenders.
#
# Container-hygiene norm (feedback_container_image_hygiene): minimize the context
# so the daemon never ships the heavy local venv / tests / evidence into the
# build, which both slows the upload and risks leaking the gitignored local .env.

# The local editable venv -- NEVER ship it (the image builds a clean venv).
.venv/
**/.venv/

# Local secrets -- the .env is gitignored AND must never enter an image layer.
# The container gets config via the task definition env + the task IAM role.
.env
*.env
.env.*

# Python build/cache artifacts.
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
**/.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
**/*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# Tests + local verification scripts + captured evidence -- not needed at
# runtime (the image runs the WS server, not the suite).
tests/
evidence/
verify_*.py
migrate_file_to_dynamo.py

# Editor / OS noise.
.DS_Store
*.swp
